<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900705-0107</DOCNO><DOCID>900705-0107.</DOCID><HL>   ADC Acquires an LPL Unit</HL><DATE>07/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   ADCT LPLI</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   MINNEAPOLIS -- ADC Telecommunications Inc. said that itacquired American Lightwave Systems Inc., a maker offiber-optic video transmission equipment and a 65%-owned unitof LPL Technologies Inc., Wallingford, Conn., for $10.7million, and that it agreed to make &quot;certain guaranteed andcontingent payments over a 3 1/2-year period&quot; totaling atleast $4 million.   ADC, which acquired LPL's 65% stake and certain AmericanLightwave employees' 35% holding, said the transaction &quot;addssignificantly&quot; to its fiber-optic capabilities and &quot;positionsus to participate in the fast-growing video-services deliverymarket.&quot; ADC said it and American Lightwave are cooperatingin providing field trials with major telephone companies ofvoice and video systems.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>